Sometimes, when I’m walking through a crowded street, I look at all the people around me and suddenly realize that each and every one of them is living a life just as vivid and complex as my own.
Each and every one of them has their own desires, their own fantasies, and their own secrets to keep.
To know every single thing about someone is near impossible, because the truth is, some secrets are buried so deep that even divulging them yourself is difficult.
My secret is one that I’ve kept for most of my life.
Whenever someone gets tied up in a movie or a book, I get excited.
It’s been that way for as long as I can remember, though when I was younger, I didn’t really understand why.
When I was six, I borrowed some scarves and pantyhose from my parents’ room and tried to tie myself up.
I remember it being somewhat of a failure, since I hadn’t really known what I was doing.
But something about me still craved that feeling of helplessness.
Maybe that’s why I was always so eager to play Cowboys and Indians with the neighborhood boys.
Whether I was a Cowboy or an Indian, the game usually ended with me tied up and gagged.
In fact, I recall that sometimes the boys would tally the score at the end by asking “Who captured Robin the most?”
Part of that was because the boys were all bigger and stronger than me, but it was mostly because I would always get caught on purpose.
Even then, I never fully got to experience that powerless feeling; though I would moan and pretend to struggle, slipping free was usually easy once the game was over.
When a new girl, Alicia, moved onto our block, I was a bit intimidated; she was loud and boisterous, and I remember watching her arm wrestle several of the boys and win.
She wanted to join in our games right away, and since she had proved herself to be just as strong as the rest of the boys, they let her.
In one game, Alicia and I wound up on opposite sides, and before long she had cornered me and bound me tightly to a tree before running off to play with the boys.
I was enjoying myself for a while, tied up to that tree, but after a long time it became apparent that the other kids had forgotten about me.
I began to get bored and tried to wriggle free, but after trying to squirm this way and that, I realized that I couldn’t move.

At first, a strange thrill ran through me. I really was totally helpless this time. No matter how hard I tried, I truly couldn’t free myself. The feeling was exhilarating—at least, it was until I remembered that no one was coming to let me go.
Panic began to replace my excitement and I struggled to get free again, to no avail. Tears had just started to slip from my eyes when Alicia finally returned, red-faced and panting.
She saw that I was crying and quickly freed me, apologizing and begging me not to tell on her. She bought us ice cream to say sorry, and from then on, we were pretty much inseparable.
She stopped all the other boys in the neighborhood from picking on me and refused to play any of their games unless they let me play too.
She also wouldn’t let them tie me up anymore when we played Cowboys and Indians because of what had happened last time, even though I told her I didn’t mind.
I was pretty disappointed about that, but as I got older, I got a lot better at tying myself up in order to fulfill my own unusual desires.
Alicia and I never really grew apart, like most childhood friends do.
We remained close all through middle school and high school, and we even decided to share an apartment while we were in university together.
It had been a while since I’d been tied up by anyone else, but I never really forgot about that day I spent tied to a tree in our old neighborhood.
Even though I’d gotten upset, looking back on it, it had still been kind of exciting to be tied up and have no idea when or if anyone was coming to set me free.
The self-bondage I did in my room was fun, but it still couldn’t replace the feeling of being tied up completely at another person’s mercy.
I had been thinking about telling Alicia my secret for a while, but like I said, it’s not easy to just blurt out.

Something that I had kept to myself for so long required a lot of mental preparation before I would be able to say it out loud, and even then, I was afraid that sharing something so personal would change our relationship.
Every time I thought about telling her, I wound up putting it off, telling myself I had to wait for the perfect moment. A moment where it would seem natural.
Now that we were living together, I knew that moment would come soon, and I wouldn’t have an excuse to get out of it.

I was constantly playing out different ways the conversation would go in my head; but I knew that no matter what she said, telling her would change the way she looked at me. I just didn’t know how much.
Tomorrow, Alicia and I are having a movie night with just the two of us.
I haven’t seen the movie before, but I know from the previews that the heroine gets captured and tied up at some point.
I wonder if Alicia feels the same way I do whenever I see that happen in movies...
Maybe I should ask her! I could even see if she would want to try tying me up...
But what if she thinks I’m a weirdo? I can’t just come right out and say something like that...
No...I’m tired of keeping it to myself all the time! I’ll just have to find a nonchalant way to bring it up.
I once read a story online about someone telling their boyfriend they liked bondage during a movie scene...why shouldn’t it work for me?
And anyway, Alicia and I have been friends forever.
Even if she’s not into the whole tying up thing, I’m sure she won’t judge me too hard...maybe...
After I finished classes the next day, I stopped by the convenience store to pick up some popcorn and snacks for our movie night.

I hadn’t been able to take my mind off it all day; I kept imagining all the different things I could say and all the different things she could say, but no matter what I did, I couldn’t stop feeling anxious about it.
But I was determined not to chicken out.
Even if Alicia did end up thinking I was weird, I couldn’t just keep this a secret anymore.
When we finally started the movie that night, I found myself unable to concentrate at all on the plot.
It felt like hours before the part I was waiting for finally came.
